name: 𝔇𝔢𝔞𝔱𝔥 𝔐𝔞𝔡𝔫𝔢𝔰𝔰
description: Have you not heard of that madman who lit a lantern in the bright morning hours, ran to the market place, and cried incessantly: "I seek God! I seek God!" -- As many of those who did not believe in God were standing around just then, he provoked much laughter. 𝔉𝔯𝔦𝔢𝔡𝔯𝔦𝔠𝔥 𝔑𝔦𝔢𝔱𝔷𝔰𝔠𝔥𝔢,  𝔗𝔥𝔢 𝔓𝔞𝔯𝔞𝔟𝔩𝔢 𝔬𝔣 𝔱𝔥𝔢 𝔐𝔞𝔡𝔪𝔞𝔫 (𝟏𝟖𝟖𝟐)
